com.github.gwtd3.api.interpolators

Interface Interpolator<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CallableInterpolator, JavascriptFunctionInterpolator, JavascriptFunctionInterpolatorDecorator

    public interface Interpolator<T>
    An interpolator is a function that maps a parametric value t in the domain [0,1] to a color, number or arbitrary value.

    D3 has many built-in interpolators to simplify the transitioning of arbitrary values; see the D3#interpolate*() methods.

    You should not directly implements this interface, but rather extend the class CallableInterpolator, if you need to pass your own interpolator to D3.

    Author:
    Anthony Schiochet
